@junyawatanabe only constant is that he's impossible to predict. For Spring/Summer 2027, the COMME des GARÇONS designer leaned all the way into hip-hop with a collection titled **"BLING BLING BLING,"** packing the runway with oversized jewelry, tracksuits, and wildly embellished caps created by artist Kota Okuda.⁠
⁠
As always, Watanabe balanced the spectacle with serious menswear, pulling together collaborators ranging from @levis, @carhartt, @newbalance, and Tricker's to newcomers like Union LA, @kappa, and even @dhlexpress. It's one of his weirdest collections in years, but that's exactly the point. Nobody in menswear keeps reinventing themselves quite like Watanabe.⁠

